track_notes: Park at the high point of the road approx SH 946 273. Plenty of space for several cars. Take the track across the road that rises diagonally to the north (right).  Basically you just stick with this main track, up and down hill for a little under 5Km to SH 987 285.  A small path leads off right/south at this point. Follow the rough path through bogs and peat hags to the summit following the fence lines. If you want to avoid the peat hags and do not mind missing the summit the Activation Zone if huge.  You can stop on the track anywhere from SH 981 283 onwards and still be in the AZ, saving nearly 2Km round trip of walking.
track_title: From west at high point on the road
